text:
TL;DR for /advocacy

/advocacy is a Warpcast-native nonprofit working to drive civic engagement around onchain technology in the U.S. through education, outreach, and grassroots advocacy.

Our Roadmap:

Electoral Advocacy & GOTV: Increase voter registration and turnout by helping people understand how and why to vote.

Research & Polling: Use real data to inform strategies in the onchain space.

Storytelling & Advocacy Training: Equip our community with tools to advocate through storytelling, messaging guides, and understanding legislative processes.

Townhalls & Education Events: Organize discussions on legislation and onchain tech benefits.

Behind the group: @clinamenic, @lish.eth, @ssj2, @oliverzerhusen, and @javabu.eth.

Fiscal Sponsorship: We are fiscally sponsored by @endaoment, allowing /advocacy to focus on its mission while still being able to accept tax-deductible donations as a 501(c)(3) nonprofit (link coming soon).

Message @advocacy to get involved or with any questions!

text:
‚ÄúWhat are you doing to help small accounts on Farcaster?‚Äù

We have a lot more work to do, but here‚Äôs what we‚Äôve done in the last few months to improve:

1. Moved initial feeds away from a follow-based model to algorithmic and interest-based model

2. A daily set of boosted accounts with <10K followers

3. USDC rewards normalized by followers

4. A bunch of experiments and tweaks to improve the home feed to show interesting casts from people you don‚Äôt follow yet

More to come!

show_title: GM Farcaster Ep156 Monday September 17, 2024 with @javabu.eth /advocacy
text:
This isn't the main reason that people aren't onboarding onto Farcaster 

Warpcast has done a poor job of creating network effects where active users try to onboard their friends.  I think many active users are discouraged to attempt to onboard their friends or social circle bc  a) it costs $5 and b) there's not enough fun things for friends to do with each other like Words With Friends, Wordle, HQ Trivia etc.

People already have too many messaging apps so I think Warpcast needs to offer messaging/social plus more fun activities in order for new users to onboard to yet another social platform or messaging app

show_title: GM Farcaster Ep156 Monday September 17, 2024 with @javabu.eth /advocacy
text:
some thoughts and questions given recent news re: "interesting content," changes to how channels work

to me, social platforms are marketplaces with "buyers" and "sellers" (in this case, of content)
- creators are "sellers" of their content goods
- enjoyoors / vibing / curators are "buyers"

as a content creator type on fc, i have expressed my concerns that the current fc algorithms punish new users too hard, which reduces possible audience sizes and makes the place not attractive to content creator types (and not fun for content consumers either!)

(i also want to emphasize that i myself am a "buyer" on other platforms like instagram, youtube, etc.! there is no value judgement to be either and we often play both roles.)

so what if instead, *user intent* is composable?
similar to how in role-playing games, you can play as characters with diff types of specialization

and it's set "per session," since sometimes I want to broadcast and share my content, and other times, support my friends with theirs

show_title: GM Farcaster Ep156 Monday September 17, 2024 with @javabu.eth /advocacy
text:
I've been thinking about the conversation about "interesting content" because it makes me wonder: what IS interesting content? Why am I here?

I came here to start from square one, largely because I didn't/don't love the noise that's in all my other web2 newsfeeds.

But when asked what kind of content I *want* to see...I don't really know. I can say what I do like so far:

- @chinmay.eth 's Guess the Movie (I like games)
- @samantha 's /humankind candles (I like buying things)
- the recs and convos in /privacy and /politics 
- @afrochicks 's content (and all real people posts) in /fitness 

I do miss the early days of /manga-anime ü•∫

So what is everyone else looking for, exactly? Could you even describe what "interesting content" looks like for you?
